        <definition>void smp_rx_remove_invalid</definition>
        <argsstring>(struct smp_transport *zst, void *arg)</argsstring>
        <name>smp_rx_remove_invalid</name>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structsmp__transport" kindref="compound">smp_transport</ref> *</type>
          <declname>zst</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>arg</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Used to remove queued requests for an SMP transport that are no longer valid. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>A <ref refid="group__mcumgr__transport__smp_1gaacb9495e395e3b763eaca70546dc9555" kindref="member">smp_transport_query_valid_check_fn()</ref> function must be registered for this to function. If the <ref refid="group__mcumgr__transport__smp_1gaacb9495e395e3b763eaca70546dc9555" kindref="member">smp_transport_query_valid_check_fn()</ref> function returns false during a callback, the queried command will classed as invalid and dropped.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>zst</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The transport to use. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>arg</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Argument provided to callback <ref refid="group__mcumgr__transport__smp_1gaacb9495e395e3b763eaca70546dc9555" kindref="member">smp_transport_query_valid_check_fn()</ref> function. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
